UNLOAD
  Move a commodity from a ship back into a harbor sector, or take a
  plane back off a carrier/sub.

SYNTAX
  unload <commodity> <ship-spec> <amount>
  unlo   <commodity> <ship-spec> <amount>
  unload plane <ship-spec> <plane-spec>

DESCRIPTION
  COMMODITIES: transfers goods from a ship's hold into the harbor
  sector where the ship is currently docked.  The ship must be in a
  harbor sector (type 'h') that you own, at least 2% efficient.

  <commodity>  - single letter: f=food c=civ m=mil l=lcm etc.
  <ship-spec>  - ship uid, range (0-5), or * for all ships in harbor
  <amount>     - how many units to unload

  If the ship has fewer than <amount>, it unloads what it has.

  PLANES: 'unload plane' takes a plane back off a ship it's currently
  aboard (matched via <ship-spec>) — no harbor needed. The plane ends
  up sitting at the ship's current sector, free-standing again; use
  'fly' from there if it needs to go somewhere else.

EXAMPLE
  unload food 0 200         take 200 food off ship 0
  unload civ 1 50           disembark 50 civilians from ship 1
  unload oil * 100          unload up to 100 oil from every ship
  unload plane 14 5         take plane 5 off ship 14

